%% seq_09_skill_profile.mmd
%% Scope: Skill management, profile viewing, spider chart
%% Backend refs:
%%   - POST /profile/skills → AddProfileSkillController → AddUserSkillCommand
%%   - PUT /profile/skills/:id → UpdateProfileSkillController → UpdateUserSkillCommand
%%   - DELETE /profile/skills/:id → RemoveProfileSkillController
%%   - GET /profile → ShowProfileController (loads skills as part of profile)
%%   - GET /users/:id/profile → ViewUserProfileController
%%   - CalculateSpiderChartCommand (standalone, not auto-triggered)
%%   - ⚠️ No GET /skills catalog route
%%   - ⚠️ No GET /profile/spider-chart route
%%   - ⚠️ No POST /bookmarks route (recruiter_bookmarks table/model exist but no route)

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User
    participant B as Browser (Svelte)
    participant C as Controller
    participant Cmd as Command
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    actor V as Viewer

    Note over U, V: === VIEW MY PROFILE (with skills) ===
    Note over C: ShowProfileController

    U->>B: Open profile page
    B->>C: GET /profile
    C->>DB: SELECT user + user_skills + skills
    C-->>B: Profile data (includes skills)
    B-->>U: Show profile + skills list

    Note over U, V: === ADD SKILL ===
    Note over C: AddProfileSkillController

    U->>B: Add new skill
    B->>C: POST /profile/skills
    C->>Cmd: AddUserSkillCommand.execute(dto)

    Cmd->>DB: Check existing user_skill
    (user_id + skill_id)

    alt Already has this skill
        Cmd-->>C: ConflictException (409)
    else New skill
        Cmd->>DB: INSERT INTO user_skills
        (user_id, skill_id, level_code,
        source='imported',
        avg_score=0, total_reviews=0)
        Cmd-->>C: UserSkill object
        C-->>B: Redirect back
    end

    Note over U, V: === UPDATE SKILL LEVEL ===
    Note over C: UpdateProfileSkillController

    U->>B: Change proficiency level
    B->>C: PUT /profile/skills/:id
    C->>Cmd: UpdateUserSkillCommand.execute(dto)
    Cmd->>DB: UPDATE user_skills
    SET level_code = ?
    WHERE id = ? AND user_id = ?
    Cmd-->>C: Updated
    C-->>B: Redirect back

    Note over U, V: === REMOVE SKILL ===
    Note over C: RemoveProfileSkillController

    U->>B: Remove skill
    B->>C: DELETE /profile/skills/:id
    C->>DB: DELETE FROM user_skills
    WHERE id = ? AND user_id = ?
    C-->>B: Redirect back

    Note over U, V: === VIEW OTHER USER PROFILE ===
    Note over C: ViewUserProfileController

    V->>B: Browse user profile
    B->>C: GET /users/:id/profile
    C->>DB: SELECT user + skills + reviews
    C-->>B: Profile data
    B-->>V: Show profile + spider chart

    Note over U, V: === SPIDER CHART ===
    Note over Cmd: CalculateSpiderChartCommand
    Note over Cmd: ⚠️ Standalone command,
    Note over Cmd: NOT auto-triggered by reviews.
    Note over Cmd: Must be called explicitly.
    Note over Cmd: Source distinction:
    Note over Cmd: 'imported' = user self-reported
    Note over Cmd: 'reviewed' = set by review system

    Note over U, V: === RECRUITER BOOKMARKS ===
    Note over Cmd: ⚠️ recruiter_bookmarks table
    Note over Cmd: and model EXIST but
    Note over Cmd: NO route/controller wired.
    Note over Cmd: Bookmark feature is NOT functional.


